29ProgramPipelineState::ProgramPipelineState()
30 : mLabel(),
31 mActiveShaderProgram(nullptr),
32 mValid(false),
33 mExecutable(new ProgramExecutable()),
34 mIsLinked(false)
35{
36 for (const ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
37 {
38 mPrograms[shaderType] = nullptr;

56
57void ProgramPipelineState::useProgramStage(const Context *context,
58 const ShaderType shaderType,
59 Program *shaderProgram,
60 angle::ObserverBinding *programObserverBindings)
61{
62 Program *oldProgram = mPrograms[shaderType];
63 if (oldProgram)
64 {
65 oldProgram->release(context);
66 }
67
68 // If program refers to a program object with a valid shader attached for the indicated shader
69 // stage, glUseProgramStages installs the executable code for that stage in the indicated
70 // program pipeline object pipeline.
71 if (shaderProgram && (shaderProgram->id().value != 0) &&
72 shaderProgram->getExecutable().hasLinkedShaderStage(shaderType))
73 {
74 mPrograms[shaderType] = shaderProgram;
75 shaderProgram->addRef();
76 }
77 else
78 {
79 // If program is zero, or refers to a program object with no valid shader executable for the
80 // given stage, it is as if the pipeline object has no programmable stage configured for the
81 // indicated shader stage.
82 mPrograms[shaderType] = nullptr;
83 }
84
85 Program *program = mPrograms[shaderType];
86 programObserverBindings->bind(program);
87}
88
89void ProgramPipelineState::useProgramStages(
90 const Context *context,
91 GLbitfield stages,
92 Program *shaderProgram,
93 std::vector<angle::ObserverBinding> *programObserverBindings)
94{
95 if (stages == GL_ALL_SHADER_BITS)
96 {
97 for (const ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
98 {
99 size_t index = static_cast<size_t>(shaderType);
100 ASSERT(index < programObserverBindings->size());
101 useProgramStage(context, shaderType, shaderProgram,
102 &programObserverBindings->at(index));
103 }
104 }
105 else
106 {
107 if (stages & GL_VERTEX_SHADER_BIT)
108 {
109 size_t index = static_cast<size_t>(ShaderType::Vertex);
110 ASSERT(index < programObserverBindings->size());
111 useProgramStage(context, ShaderType::Vertex, shaderProgram,
112 &programObserverBindings->at(index));
113 }
114
115 if (stages & GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER_BIT)
116 {
117 size_t index = static_cast<size_t>(ShaderType::Fragment);
118 ASSERT(index < programObserverBindings->size());
119 useProgramStage(context, ShaderType::Fragment, shaderProgram,
120 &programObserverBindings->at(index));
121 }
122
123 if (stages & GL_COMPUTE_SHADER_BIT)
124 {
125 size_t index = static_cast<size_t>(ShaderType::Compute);
126 ASSERT(index < programObserverBindings->size());
127 useProgramStage(context, ShaderType::Compute, shaderProgram,
128 &programObserverBindings->at(index));
129 }
130 }
131}
132
133bool ProgramPipelineState::usesShaderProgram(ShaderProgramID programId) const
134{
135 for (const Program *program : mPrograms)
136 {
137 if (program && (program->id() == programId))
138 {
139 return true;
140 }
141 }
142
143 return false;
144}
145
146void ProgramPipelineState::updateExecutableTextures()
147{
148 for (const ShaderType shaderType : mExecutable->getLinkedShaderStages())
149 {
150 const Program *program = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
151 ASSERT(program);
152 mExecutable->setActiveTextureMask(program->getExecutable().getActiveSamplersMask());
153 mExecutable->setActiveImagesMask(program->getExecutable().getActiveImagesMask());
154 // Updates mActiveSamplerRefCounts, mActiveSamplerTypes, and mActiveSamplerFormats
155 mExecutable->updateActiveSamplers(program->getState());
156 }
157}
158
159ProgramPipeline::ProgramPipeline(rx::GLImplFactory *factory, ProgramPipelineID handle)
160 : RefCountObject(factory->generateSerial(), handle),
161 mProgramPipelineImpl(factory->createProgramPipeline(mState)),
162 mExecutableObserverBinding(this, kExecutableSubjectIndex)
163{
164 ASSERT(mProgramPipelineImpl);
165
166 for (const ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
167 {
168 mProgramObserverBindings.emplace_back(this, static_cast<angle::SubjectIndex>(shaderType));
169 }
170 mExecutableObserverBinding.bind(mState.mExecutable);
171}
172
173ProgramPipeline::~ProgramPipeline()
174{
175 mProgramPipelineImpl.release();
176}

178void ProgramPipeline::onDestroy(const Context *context)
179{
180 for (Program *program : mState.mPrograms)
181 {
182 if (program)
183 {
184 ASSERT(program->getRefCount());
185 program->release(context);
186 }
187 }
188
189 getImplementation()->destroy(context);
190}

212void ProgramPipeline::useProgramStages(const Context *context,
213 GLbitfield stages,
214 Program *shaderProgram)
215{
216 mState.useProgramStages(context, stages, shaderProgram, &mProgramObserverBindings);
217 updateLinkedShaderStages();
218 updateExecutable();
219
220 mState.mIsLinked = false;
221}
222
223void ProgramPipeline::updateLinkedShaderStages()
224{
225 mState.mExecutable->resetLinkedShaderStages();
226
227 for (const ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
228 {
229 Program *program = mState.mPrograms[shaderType];
230 if (program)
231 {
232 mState.mExecutable->setLinkedShaderStages(shaderType);
233 }
234 }
235
236 mState.mExecutable->updateCanDrawWith();
237}
238
239void ProgramPipeline::updateExecutableAttributes()
240{
241 Program *vertexProgram = getShaderProgram(gl::ShaderType::Vertex);
242
243 if (!vertexProgram)
244 {
245 return;
246 }
247
248 const ProgramExecutable &vertexExecutable = vertexProgram->getExecutable();
249 mState.mExecutable->mActiveAttribLocationsMask = vertexExecutable.mActiveAttribLocationsMask;
250 mState.mExecutable->mMaxActiveAttribLocation = vertexExecutable.mMaxActiveAttribLocation;
251 mState.mExecutable->mAttributesTypeMask = vertexExecutable.mAttributesTypeMask;
252 mState.mExecutable->mAttributesMask = vertexExecutable.mAttributesMask;
253}

255void ProgramPipeline::updateTransformFeedbackMembers()
256{
257 Program *vertexProgram = getShaderProgram(gl::ShaderType::Vertex);
258
259 if (!vertexProgram)
260 {
261 return;
262 }
263
264 const ProgramExecutable &vertexExecutable = vertexProgram->getExecutable();
265 mState.mExecutable->mTransformFeedbackStrides = vertexExecutable.mTransformFeedbackStrides;
266 mState.mExecutable->mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings =
267 vertexExecutable.mLinkedTransformFeedbackVaryings;
268}
269
270void ProgramPipeline::updateShaderStorageBlocks()
271{
272 mState.mExecutable->mComputeShaderStorageBlocks.clear();
273 mState.mExecutable->mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks.clear();
274
275 // Only copy the storage blocks from each Program in the PPO once, since each Program could
276 // contain multiple shader stages.
277 ShaderBitSet handledStages;
278
279 for (const gl::ShaderType shaderType : kAllGraphicsShaderTypes)
280 {
281 const Program *shaderProgram = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
282 if (shaderProgram && !handledStages.test(shaderType))
283 {
284 // Only add each Program's blocks once.
285 handledStages |= shaderProgram->getExecutable().getLinkedShaderStages();
286
287 for (const InterfaceBlock &block :
288 shaderProgram->getExecutable().getShaderStorageBlocks())
289 {
290 mState.mExecutable->mGraphicsShaderStorageBlocks.emplace_back(block);
291 }
292 }
293 }
294
295 const Program *computeProgram = getShaderProgram(ShaderType::Compute);
296 if (computeProgram)
297 {
298 for (const InterfaceBlock &block : computeProgram->getExecutable().getShaderStorageBlocks())
299 {
300 mState.mExecutable->mComputeShaderStorageBlocks.emplace_back(block);
301 }
302 }
303}
304
305void ProgramPipeline::updateImageBindings()
306{
307 mState.mExecutable->mComputeImageBindings.clear();
308 mState.mExecutable->mGraphicsImageBindings.clear();
309
310 // Only copy the storage blocks from each Program in the PPO once, since each Program could
311 // contain multiple shader stages.
312 ShaderBitSet handledStages;
313
314 for (const gl::ShaderType shaderType : kAllGraphicsShaderTypes)
315 {
316 const Program *shaderProgram = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
317 if (shaderProgram && !handledStages.test(shaderType))
318 {
319 // Only add each Program's blocks once.
320 handledStages |= shaderProgram->getExecutable().getLinkedShaderStages();
321
322 for (const ImageBinding &imageBinding : shaderProgram->getState().getImageBindings())
323 {
324 mState.mExecutable->mGraphicsImageBindings.emplace_back(imageBinding);
325 }
326 }
327 }
328
329 const Program *computeProgram = getShaderProgram(ShaderType::Compute);
330 if (computeProgram)
331 {
332 for (const ImageBinding &imageBinding : computeProgram->getState().getImageBindings())
333 {
334 mState.mExecutable->mComputeImageBindings.emplace_back(imageBinding);
335 }
336 }
337}
338
339void ProgramPipeline::updateHasBooleans()
340{
341 // Need to check all of the shader stages, not just linked, so we handle Compute correctly.
342 for (const gl::ShaderType shaderType : kAllGraphicsShaderTypes)
343 {
344 const Program *shaderProgram = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
345 if (shaderProgram)
346 {
347 const ProgramExecutable &executable = shaderProgram->getExecutable();
348
349 if (executable.hasUniformBuffers())
350 {
351 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasGraphicsUniformBuffers = true;
352 }
353 if (executable.hasGraphicsStorageBuffers())
354 {
355 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasGraphicsStorageBuffers = true;
356 }
357 if (executable.hasAtomicCounterBuffers())
358 {
359 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasGraphicsAtomicCounterBuffers = true;
360 }
361 if (executable.hasDefaultUniforms())
362 {
363 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasGraphicsDefaultUniforms = true;
364 }
365 if (executable.hasTextures())
366 {
367 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasGraphicsTextures = true;
368 }
369 if (executable.hasGraphicsImages())
370 {
371 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasGraphicsImages = true;
372 }
373 }
374 }
375
376 const Program *computeProgram = getShaderProgram(ShaderType::Compute);
377 if (computeProgram)
378 {
379 const ProgramExecutable &executable = computeProgram->getExecutable();
380
381 if (executable.hasUniformBuffers())
382 {
383 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasComputeUniformBuffers = true;
384 }
385 if (executable.hasComputeStorageBuffers())
386 {
387 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasComputeStorageBuffers = true;
388 }
389 if (executable.hasAtomicCounterBuffers())
390 {
391 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasComputeAtomicCounterBuffers = true;
392 }
393 if (executable.hasDefaultUniforms())
394 {
395 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasComputeDefaultUniforms = true;
396 }
397 if (executable.hasTextures())
398 {
399 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasComputeTextures = true;
400 }
401 if (executable.hasComputeImages())
402 {
403 mState.mExecutable->mPipelineHasComputeImages = true;
404 }
405 }
406}

408void ProgramPipeline::updateExecutable()
409{
410 mState.mExecutable->reset();
411
412 // Vertex Shader ProgramExecutable properties
413 updateExecutableAttributes();
414 updateTransformFeedbackMembers();
415 updateShaderStorageBlocks();
416 updateImageBindings();
417
418 // All Shader ProgramExecutable properties
419 mState.updateExecutableTextures();
420
421 // Must be last, since it queries things updated by earlier functions
422 updateHasBooleans();
423}
424
425ProgramMergedVaryings ProgramPipeline::getMergedVaryings() const
426{
427 ASSERT(!mState.mExecutable->isCompute());
428
429 // Varyings are matched between pairs of consecutive stages, by location if assigned or
430 // by name otherwise. Note that it's possible for one stage to specify location and the other
431 // not: https://cvs.khronos.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=16261
432
433 // Map stages to the previous active stage in the rendering pipeline. When looking at input
434 // varyings of a stage, this is used to find the stage whose output varyings are being linked
435 // with them.
436 ShaderMap<ShaderType> previousActiveStage;
437
438 // Note that kAllGraphicsShaderTypes is sorted according to the rendering pipeline.
439 ShaderType lastActiveStage = ShaderType::InvalidEnum;
440 for (ShaderType shaderType : getExecutable().getLinkedShaderStages())
441 {
442 previousActiveStage[shaderType] = lastActiveStage;
443
444 const Program *program = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
445 ASSERT(program);
446 lastActiveStage = shaderType;
447 }
448
449 // First, go through output varyings and create two maps (one by name, one by location) for
450 // faster lookup when matching input varyings.
451
452 ShaderMap<std::map<std::string, size_t>> outputVaryingNameToIndexShaderMap;
453 ShaderMap<std::map<int, size_t>> outputVaryingLocationToIndexShaderMap;
454
455 ProgramMergedVaryings merged;
456
457 // Gather output varyings.
458 for (ShaderType shaderType : getExecutable().getLinkedShaderStages())
459 {
460 const Program *program = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
461 ASSERT(program);
462 Shader *shader = program->getState().getAttachedShader(shaderType);
463 ASSERT(shader);
464
465 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : shader->getOutputVaryings())
466 {
467 merged.push_back({});
468 ProgramVaryingRef *ref = &merged.back();
469
470 ref->frontShader = &varying;
471 ref->frontShaderStage = shaderType;
472
473 // Always map by name. Even if location is provided in this stage, it may not be in the
474 // paired stage.
475 outputVaryingNameToIndexShaderMap[shaderType][varying.name] = merged.size() - 1;
476
477 // If location is provided, also keep it in a map by location.
478 if (varying.location != -1)
479 {
480 outputVaryingLocationToIndexShaderMap[shaderType][varying.location] =
481 merged.size() - 1;
482 }
483 }
484 }
485
486 // Gather input varyings, and match them with output varyings of the previous stage.
487 for (ShaderType shaderType : getExecutable().getLinkedShaderStages())
488 {
489 const Program *program = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
490 ASSERT(program);
491 Shader *shader = program->getState().getAttachedShader(shaderType);
492 ASSERT(shader);
493 ShaderType previousStage = previousActiveStage[shaderType];
494
495 for (const sh::ShaderVariable &varying : shader->getInputVaryings())
496 {
497 size_t mergedIndex = merged.size();
498 if (previousStage != ShaderType::InvalidEnum)
499 {
500 // If location is provided, see if we can match by location.
501 if (varying.location != -1)
502 {
503 std::map<int, size_t> outputVaryingLocationToIndex =
504 outputVaryingLocationToIndexShaderMap[previousStage];
505 auto byLocationIter = outputVaryingLocationToIndex.find(varying.location);
506 if (byLocationIter != outputVaryingLocationToIndex.end())
507 {
508 mergedIndex = byLocationIter->second;
509 }
510 }
511
512 // If not found, try to match by name.
513 if (mergedIndex == merged.size())
514 {
515 std::map<std::string, size_t> outputVaryingNameToIndex =
516 outputVaryingNameToIndexShaderMap[previousStage];
517 auto byNameIter = outputVaryingNameToIndex.find(varying.name);
518 if (byNameIter != outputVaryingNameToIndex.end())
519 {
520 mergedIndex = byNameIter->second;
521 }
522 }
523 }
524
525 // If no previous stage, or not matched by location or name, create a new entry for it.
526 if (mergedIndex == merged.size())
527 {
528 merged.push_back({});
529 mergedIndex = merged.size() - 1;
530 }
531
532 ProgramVaryingRef *ref = &merged[mergedIndex];
533
534 ref->backShader = &varying;
535 ref->backShaderStage = shaderType;
536 }
537 }
538
539 return merged;
540}

542// The attached shaders are checked for linking errors by matching up their variables.
543// Uniform, input and output variables get collected.
544// The code gets compiled into binaries.
545angle::Result ProgramPipeline::link(const Context *context)
546{
547 if (mState.mIsLinked)
548 {
549 return angle::Result::Continue;
550 }
551
552 ProgramMergedVaryings mergedVaryings;
553
554 if (!getExecutable().isCompute())
555 {
556 InfoLog &infoLog = mState.mExecutable->getInfoLog();
557 infoLog.reset();
558 const State &state = context->getState();
559
560 // Map the varyings to the register file
561 gl::PackMode packMode = PackMode::ANGLE_RELAXED;
562 if (state.getLimitations().noFlexibleVaryingPacking)
563 {
564 // D3D9 pack mode is strictly more strict than WebGL, so takes priority.
565 packMode = PackMode::ANGLE_NON_CONFORMANT_D3D9;
566 }
567 else if (state.getExtensions().webglCompatibility)
568 {
569 // In WebGL, we use a slightly different handling for packing variables.
570 packMode = PackMode::WEBGL_STRICT;
571 }
572
573 if (!linkVaryings(infoLog))
574 {
575 return angle::Result::Stop;
576 }
577
578 gl::ShaderMap<const gl::ProgramState *> programStates;
579 fillProgramStateMap(&programStates);
580 if (!mState.mExecutable->linkValidateGlobalNames(infoLog, programStates))
581 {
582 return angle::Result::Stop;
583 }
584
585 GLuint maxVaryingVectors =
586 static_cast<GLuint>(context->getState().getCaps().maxVaryingVectors);
587 VaryingPacking varyingPacking(maxVaryingVectors, packMode);
588
589 mergedVaryings = getMergedVaryings();
590 for (ShaderType shaderType : getExecutable().getLinkedShaderStages())
591 {
592 Program *program = mState.mPrograms[shaderType];
593 ASSERT(program);
594 program->getExecutable().getResources().varyingPacking.reset();
595 ANGLE_TRY(
596 program->linkMergedVaryings(context, program->getExecutable(), mergedVaryings));
597 }
598 }
599
600 ANGLE_TRY(getImplementation()->link(context, mergedVaryings));
601
602 mState.mIsLinked = true;
603
604 return angle::Result::Continue;
605}
606
607bool ProgramPipeline::linkVaryings(InfoLog &infoLog) const
608{
609 ShaderType previousShaderType = ShaderType::InvalidEnum;
610 for (ShaderType shaderType : getExecutable().getLinkedShaderStages())
611 {
612 Program *program = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
613 ASSERT(program);
614 ProgramExecutable &executable = program->getExecutable();
615
616 if (previousShaderType != ShaderType::InvalidEnum)
617 {
618 Program *previousProgram = getShaderProgram(previousShaderType);
619 ASSERT(previousProgram);
620 ProgramExecutable &previousExecutable = previousProgram->getExecutable();
621
622 if (!Program::linkValidateShaderInterfaceMatching(
623 previousExecutable.getLinkedOutputVaryings(previousShaderType),
624 executable.getLinkedInputVaryings(shaderType), previousShaderType, shaderType,
625 previousExecutable.getLinkedShaderVersion(previousShaderType),
626 executable.getLinkedShaderVersion(shaderType), true, infoLog))
627 {
628 return false;
629 }
630 }
631 previousShaderType = shaderType;
632 }
633
634 Program *vertexProgram = mState.mPrograms[ShaderType::Vertex];
635 Program *fragmentProgram = mState.mPrograms[ShaderType::Fragment];
636 if (!vertexProgram || !fragmentProgram)
637 {
638 return false;
639 }
640 ProgramExecutable &vertexExecutable = vertexProgram->getExecutable();
641 ProgramExecutable &fragmentExecutable = fragmentProgram->getExecutable();
642 return Program::linkValidateBuiltInVaryings(
643 vertexExecutable.getLinkedOutputVaryings(ShaderType::Vertex),
644 fragmentExecutable.getLinkedInputVaryings(ShaderType::Fragment),
645 vertexExecutable.getLinkedShaderVersion(ShaderType::Vertex), infoLog);
646}

648void ProgramPipeline::validate(const gl::Context *context)
649{
650 const Caps &caps = context->getCaps();
651 mState.mValid = true;
652 InfoLog &infoLog = mState.mExecutable->getInfoLog();
653 infoLog.reset();
654
655 for (const ShaderType shaderType : mState.mExecutable->getLinkedShaderStages())
656 {
657 Program *shaderProgram = mState.mPrograms[shaderType];
658 if (shaderProgram)
659 {
660 shaderProgram->resolveLink(context);
661 shaderProgram->validate(caps);
662 std::string shaderInfoString = shaderProgram->getExecutable().getInfoLogString();
663 if (shaderInfoString.length())
664 {
665 mState.mValid = false;
666 infoLog << shaderInfoString << "\n";
667 return;
668 }
669 if (!shaderProgram->isSeparable())
670 {
671 mState.mValid = false;
672 infoLog << GetShaderTypeString(shaderType) << " is not marked separable."
673 << "\n";
674 return;
675 }
676 }
677 }
678
679 if (!linkVaryings(infoLog))
680 {
681 mState.mValid = false;
682
683 for (const ShaderType shaderType : mState.mExecutable->getLinkedShaderStages())
684 {
685 Program *shaderProgram = mState.mPrograms[shaderType];
686 ASSERT(shaderProgram);
687 shaderProgram->validate(caps);
688 std::string shaderInfoString = shaderProgram->getExecutable().getInfoLogString();
689 if (shaderInfoString.length())
690 {
691 infoLog << shaderInfoString << "\n";
692 }
693 }
694 }
695}
696
697bool ProgramPipeline::validateSamplers(InfoLog *infoLog, const Caps &caps)
698{
699 for (const ShaderType shaderType : gl::AllShaderTypes())
700 {
701 Program *shaderProgram = mState.mPrograms[shaderType];
702 if (shaderProgram && !shaderProgram->validateSamplers(infoLog, caps))
703 {
704 return false;
705 }
706 }
707
708 return true;
709}
710
711void ProgramPipeline::onSubjectStateChange(angle::SubjectIndex index, angle::SubjectMessage message)
712{
713 switch (message)
714 {
715 case angle::SubjectMessage::SubjectChanged:
716 mState.mIsLinked = false;
717 mState.updateExecutableTextures();
718 break;
719 default:
720 UNREACHABLE();
721 break;
722 }
723}
724
725void ProgramPipeline::fillProgramStateMap(ShaderMap<const ProgramState *> *programStatesOut)
726{
727 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
728 {
729 (*programStatesOut)[shaderType] = nullptr;
730
731 Program *program = getShaderProgram(shaderType);
732 if (program)
733 {
734 (*programStatesOut)[shaderType] = &program->getState();
735 }
736 }
737}
